body:
Hello!

When trying to force a memory element using an integer literal (or a variable with a width of 1 bit) as an index, an error `error: invalid types 'CData {aka unsigned char}[unsigned int]' for array subscript` occurs at compile time. This error does not occur if you use a variable with a width greater than one bit.

**Success (use multi-bit variable as index):**

```systemverilog
module example_1;
  bit memory[3];
  bit [1:0] index = 0;

  initial begin
    force memory[index] = 1;
    release memory;

    #1;
    $display(memory[0]);
    $finish();
  end
endmodule
```

Command: `verilator --binary -j 0 -Wall example_1.sv`

**Failure (use literal as index):**

```systemverilog
module example_2;
  bit memory[3];

  initial begin
    force memory[0] = 1;
    release memory;

    #1;
    $display(memory[0]);
    $finish();
  end
endmodule
```

Command: `verilator --binary -j 0 -Wall example_2.sv`

Output:

```text
echo "" > Vexample_2__ALL.verilator_deplist.tmp
In file included from Vexample_2__ALL.cpp:5:
Vexample_2___024root__DepSet_h3de49710__0.cpp: In function 'VlCoroutine Vexample_2___024root___eval_initial__TOP__Vtiming__0(Vexample_2___024root*)':
Vexample_2___024root__DepSet_h3de49710__0.cpp:25:45: error: invalid types 'CData {aka unsigned char}[unsigned int]' for array subscript
   25 |     vlSelf->example_2__DOT__memory__VforceEn[0U] = 1U;
      |                                             ^
make: *** [/usr/local/share/verilator/include/verilated.mk:266: Vexample_2__ALL.o] Error 1
```

**Failure (use single-bit variable as index):**

```systemverilog
module example_3;
  bit memory[2];
  bit index = 0;

  initial begin
    force memory[index] = 1;
    release memory;

    #1;
    $display(memory[0]);
    $finish();
  end
endmodule
```

Command: `verilator --binary -j 0 -Wall example_3.sv`

Output:

```text
echo "" > Vexample_3__ALL.verilator_deplist.tmp
In file included from Vexample_3__ALL.cpp:5:
Vexample_3___024root__DepSet_hf1c8cca3__0.cpp: In function 'VlCoroutine Vexample_3___024root___eval_initial__TOP__Vtiming__0(Vexample_3___024root*)':
Vexample_3___024root__DepSet_hf1c8cca3__0.cpp:25:45: error: invalid types 'CData {aka unsigned char}[unsigned int]' for array subscript
   25 |     vlSelf->example_3__DOT__memory__VforceEn[0U] = 1U;
      |                                             ^
make: *** [/usr/local/share/verilator/include/verilated.mk:266: Vexample_3__ALL.o] Error 1
```

---

Verilator version (git master): `Verilator 5.021 devel rev UNKNOWN.REV`

OS (verilator devcontainer): Ubuntu 22.04.3 LTS
